<TITLE> Paranavitana and Dilshan give Sri Lanka solid start </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 MUMBAI, Dec 2 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Openers Tharanga Paranavitana and Tillakaratne Dilshan provided Sri Lanka with a solid start in their bid for a series-levelling victory in the third and final Test against India Wednesday. Left-handed Paranavitana hit a breezy 53 and Dilshan raced to 51 not out to take the tourists to 117 for one at lunch after they won the toss and chose to bat first at the Brabourne Stadium. Paranavitana struck seven fours while Dilshan was punishing on anything short as he blasted Shanthakumaran Sreesanth for a six and a four off successive deliveries to make his intentions clear on a good batting pitch. But the opening partnership was halted by spinner Harbhajan Singh, who helped stem the flow of runs with some flat, accurate bowling which claimed the wicket of Paranavitana caught behind by Rahul Dravid. Captain Kumar Sangakkara (10) was at the crease with Dilshan at the break after Paranavitana fell following his first fifty of the tour. Sri Lanka are yet to record a test win on Indian soil since their first visit in 1982 and are trailing 1-0 in the series after losing the second Test by an innings and 144 ru
